<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,287,1475,1500]" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Biology</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="207" pageNumber="208" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="207.[151,1436,719,1572]" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1511,1536]" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Distribution</emphasis>
. Southeastern and northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[732,791,1512,1536]" name="Cuba" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[812,916,1512,1536]" captionStart="FIGURES 369–376" captionStartId="283.[151,258,1972,1993]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,195,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-65@283.[151,1398,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="283" captionText="FIGURES 369–376. Distribution maps for species of Messatoporus. 369 M. townesi. 370, M. transversostriatus. 371, M. unidentatus. 372, M. unimaculatus. 373, M. variegatus. 374, M. versicolor. 375, M. xanthogaster. 376, M. zonatus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5262241" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5262241/files/figure.png" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Fig. 376</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[940,1196,1513,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Messatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonatus">
<emphasis box="[940,1196,1513,1536]" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Messatoporus zonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to occur in sympatry with the other Cuban species, 
<taxonomicName box="[599,722,1549,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Messatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="townesi">
<emphasis box="[599,722,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">M. townesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, at least at one of its recorded localities (
<collectingRegion box="[1181,1385,1548,1572]" country="Cuba" name="Santiago de Cuba" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Santiago de Cuba</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
